<b>Lesson 1 Notes</b> <br><br>

Basics of the Web<br>
1. the web - major pieces, what they look like, how they fit together<br>
2. HTML - main document type<br>
3. URLs - how to refer to docs on the web<br>
4. HTTP - protcol web runs on<br>
5. web applications<br><br>

<em>Major pieces</em><br><br>

computer&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Internet&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;HTTP&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;servers<br>
browser<br><br>

<em>HTML - made up of</em><br>
1. text content - what you see<br>
2. markup - what it looks like<br>
3. references to other docs  ie)images, videos<br>
4. links to other pages<br><br>

<em>HTML - markup</em><br>
 &lt;NAME&gt; contents &lt;NAME&gt;     called element<br><br>

<em>HTML - Tags</em><br>
&lt; b  &gt;   bold<br>
&lt; em  &gt; emphasis - italics<br><br>

<em>HTML attributes</em><br>
&lt; TAG ATTR = "value"&gt; contents &lt;TAG &gt;><br>
ex) &lt;a href = "www.reddit.com"&gt derp &lt;a &gt; <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;ATTR = attribute name<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;value = url<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;derp = what will show on screen<br><br>

<em>HTML images&gt;</em><br>
&lt;img src="url" alt="text"&gt;<br>
note - no closing tag - called void tag<br><br>

<em>HTML white space</em><br>
&lt;br>  break - void tag<br>
&lt;p> content p&gt;  paragraph<br><br>

<em>Inline or Block</em><br>
&lt;br>  is inline<br>
&lt;p>   is block - can have a vertical and horizontal definition<br><br>

<em>Span and Div</em><br>
&lt;span class="foo"&gt;   inline <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;text <br>
&lt;/span &gt; <br><br>

&lt;div  class="bar"&gt;    block<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;text <br>
&lt; /div &gt;<br><br>

HTML Documents<br>
&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML&gt;<br>
&lt;html&gt;<br>
&lt;head&gt;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  &lt;title&gt;  "Title" &lt;title&gt;<br>
&lt;/head&gt;<br>
&lt;body&gt;<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  &lt;b&gt; "content" </&gt;<br>
&lt;/body&gt;<br>
&lt;/html&gt;<br><br>


example of inserting code 
Title - <title> </title>
The title tag defines the title that will appear in the title bar of your web browser. The title must appear between the head tags.


	<dt>Title - <code class="def">&lt;title&gt; &lt;/title&gt;</code></dt>
	<dd>The <code>title</code> tag defines the title that will appear in the title bar of your web browser.  The <code>title</code> must appear 
	between the <code>head</code> tags.</dd>

